26/* This is a generic POSIX implementation of a mutex synchronization
27 mechanism for libgomp. This type is private to the library. */
28
29#ifndef GOMP_PTRLOCK_H
30#define GOMP_PTRLOCK_H 1
31
32typedef struct { void *ptr; gomp_mutex_t lock; } gomp_ptrlock_t;
33
34static inline void gomp_ptrlock_init (gomp_ptrlock_t *ptrlock, void *ptr)
35{
36 ptrlock->ptr = ptr;
37 gomp_mutex_init (&ptrlock->lock);
38}
39
40static inline void *gomp_ptrlock_get (gomp_ptrlock_t *ptrlock)
41{
42 if (ptrlock->ptr != NULL)
43 return ptrlock->ptr;
44
45 gomp_mutex_lock (&ptrlock->lock);
46 if (ptrlock->ptr != NULL)
47 {
48 gomp_mutex_unlock (&ptrlock->lock);
49 return ptrlock->ptr;
50 }
51
52 return NULL;
53}
54
55static inline void gomp_ptrlock_set (gomp_ptrlock_t *ptrlock, void *ptr)
56{
57 ptrlock->ptr = ptr;
58 gomp_mutex_unlock (&ptrlock->lock);
59}
60
61static inline void gomp_ptrlock_destroy (gomp_ptrlock_t *ptrlock)
62{
63 gomp_mutex_destroy (&ptrlock->lock);
64}
65
66#endif /* GOMP_PTRLOCK_H */
